<div id="review_4021808705" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4021808705" />
    <a title="Sofia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/114413220-sofia"><img alt="Sofia" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1607792875p2/114413220.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4021808705?book_show_action=true">May 26, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sofia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sofia" href="/user/show/114413220-sofia">Sofia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114413220-sofia?shelf=disappointments">disappointments</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114413220-sofia?shelf=lol-what-female-characters">lol-what-female-characters</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114413220-sofia?shelf=problematic">problematic</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114413220-sofia?shelf=le-sigh">le-sigh</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114413220-sofia?shelf=idek-anymore-guys">idek-anymore-guys</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114413220-sofia?shelf=failed-romance">failed-romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114413220-sofia?shelf=i-am-disgusted">i-am-disgusted</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114413220-sofia?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114413220-sofia?shelf=a-man-saves-the-day">a-man-saves-the-day</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114413220-sofia?shelf=look-at-the-idiot">look-at-the-idiot</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4021808705" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer531854326334715862">This is a story of hypocrisy and objectification.<br/><br/><br/><i>Balzac and the Little Chinese Seamstress</i> is a book about... who knows. I thought it would be about music. It&apos;s not. I thought it would be about literature. It&apos;s not. It&apos;s about two immature boys and their love for a girl named Little Seamstress. They found some books along the way and managed to make them offensive, but that was mostly a side plot. <br/><br/><br/>I think the message is supposed to be that a love for literature can open your eyes to different wor</span>
  <span id="freeText531854326334715862" style="display:none">This is a story of hypocrisy and objectification.<br /><br /><br /><i>Balzac and the Little Chinese Seamstress</i> is a book about... who knows. I thought it would be about music. It's not. I thought it would be about literature. It's not. It's about two immature boys and their love for a girl named Little Seamstress. They found some books along the way and managed to make them offensive, but that was mostly a side plot. <br /><br /><br />I think the message is supposed to be that a love for literature can open your eyes to different worlds. But it was done very badly. First of all, this was somehow twisted and became problematic. Little Seamstress hadn't yet read Western literature, so the two boys kept talking about her like she was a different species of human. Like she was so much less than they were, just a "wild mountain girl" and a "savage." <br /><br /><br />It promotes the idea that people who haven't read Western literature are nothing more than savage uncultured folk who need to be "educated." Which is ironic because this is supposed to be a criticism of reeducation. <br /><br /><br />The Little Seamstress was objectified constantly. Does she actually have a personality? No one knows. She is just a pair of pretty almond-shaped bright eyes like sTaRs and a nice face. She's the only important female character, too. Come on. This is why I try to stay away from older books by men. There was mansplaining, of course. Did you think there wouldn't be? <i>Balzac and the Little Chinese Seamstress</i> is so obviously written by a man. <br /><br /><br />The writing was supposed to be poetic, but it fell short. The dialogue was so unnatural that it made me cringe. One character was written as a great storyteller, but everything he said felt like scripted dialogue. However, this might just be a translation issue. <br /><br /><br /><br />1 star; stAY AWAY<br /><br /><br /><br /><blockquote><b>✰ Asian readathon ✰</b> <br /><br />I can't believe I started out my Asian readathon this way. It makes me feel so bad to rate a book one star when I'm just getting started. Oh, well. <br /><br />Book 1: <i>Balzac and the Little Chinese Seamstress: </i>★☆☆☆☆<br />Book 2:<i> Jade City (currently reading) </i></blockquote></span>
  <a data-text-id="531854326334715862" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


