<div id="review_11778029" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/11778029" />
    <a title="Krista the Krazy Kataloguer" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/316102-krista-the-krazy-kataloguer"><img alt="Krista the Krazy Kataloguer" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1191519600p2/316102.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/11778029?book_show_action=true">Jun 18, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Krista the Krazy Kataloguer" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Krista the Krazy Kataloguer" href="/user/show/316102-krista-the-krazy-kataloguer">Krista the Krazy Kataloguer</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/316102-krista-the-krazy-kataloguer?shelf=read-iic">read-iic</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/316102-krista-the-krazy-kataloguer?shelf=read-historical-fiction">read-historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/316102-krista-the-krazy-kataloguer?shelf=read-adult-fiction">read-adult-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer11778029" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10044100768309671959">Set in 1971 during China&apos;s Cultural Revolution, this is the story of two teenage boys sent to be &quot;re-educated&quot; in a remote mountain village. I expected it to be a rather grim tale, but it wasn&apos;t. These city boys do suffer under the heavy workloads of the peasants, but they also find time to visit friends in other villages, one of whom is a teenage peasant girl known as the Little Seamstress, and another of whom is a city boy like themselves called Four-Eyes. When they discover that Four-Eyes has</span>
  <span id="freeText10044100768309671959" style="display:none">Set in 1971 during China's Cultural Revolution, this is the story of two teenage boys sent to be "re-educated" in a remote mountain village. I expected it to be a rather grim tale, but it wasn't. These city boys do suffer under the heavy workloads of the peasants, but they also find time to visit friends in other villages, one of whom is a teenage peasant girl known as the Little Seamstress, and another of whom is a city boy like themselves called Four-Eyes. When they discover that Four-Eyes has a secret suitcase full of forbidden western classics, they borrow and eventually steal the books. One of the boys, Luo, who is in love with the Little Seamstress, introduces her to western ideas by reading Balzac to her. What follows is a look at how literature can uplift, enlighten, and inspire, but not necessarily for the good. The book does not end the way you think it will. There is a great deal of irony in the ending. <br /><br />I would love to use this novel for a book discussion. There is so much to talk about here. It amazed me that living conditions could be so un-technological and people so ignorant as to not know the capital of their own country in such a modern time. I hope it's not still this way in China today. The author's description of some of the forbidden classics, mostly by French authors, was so appealing that I wanted to run out and grab some Balzac and Dumas to read myself. Once I started reading this novel, I couldn't put it down. I would love to read more about the adventures of these two teenage boys in their peasant village. Are they ever allowed to return to the city? Do they ever find more forbidden books to read? Do they marry and stay in the village? Alas, I don't think any sequels were written. <br /><br />Highly recommended--a quick, enjoyable read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10044100768309671959" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


